<TITLE> Salam Pintu refused bail, Nasiruddin Pintu granted </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)The High Court has refused former BNP deputy minister Abdus Salam Pintu bail but former MP Nasiruddin Ahmed Pintu secured bail in separate cases. The bench of justices Siddiqur Rahman Mian and Krishna Debnath gave the order on Monday following the plea filed by Salam Pintu on Mar 7 in a case over bomb attack on the Chashara Awami League office. The bomb attack on on June 16, 2001 left 20 people dead and about 50 Awami League members including former party MP Shamim Osman injured. The case was filed on the following day. Salam was shown arrested in the case on Nov 9 last year. Khandaker Mahbub Hossain argued for the defendants, while the attorney general for the prosecution. Meanwhile, the High Court bench of justices Sheikh Rezwan Ali and Habibul Gani the same day granted ex-BNP lawmaker Nasiruddin Pintu bail in the BDR mutiny case. Pintu was arrested on June 2 at the High Court premises on charges of abetting BDR mutineers escape border force's Peelkhana headquarters during the mutiny last year. bdnews2
